<b>Response of the Government of the Sudan 
</b></p>
<p><b>The 2009 Press Act was promulgated. It 
provides for an automatic licensing for 
newspapers, prohibits the detention or 
harassment of a journalist because of his 
opinion.  
</b></p>
<p><b>Since the inception of the Act no cases were 
reported pertaining to arrest or threatening of 
a journalist.  
</b></p>
<p><b>Pre-printing censorship was immediately 
lifted following the promulgation of the Press 
Act.  
</b></p>
<p><b>An elected Press Council was established  
</b></p>
<p><b>Political Parties were licensed to issue their 
own independent newspapers. </b></p>

